1
00:00:09,287 --> 00:00:13,888
(This program is intended for mature audiences.
It may feature explicit content, violence, and strong language)

2
00:00:13,888 --> 00:00:20,267
(All characters, places, and events
in this series are entirely fictitious)

3
00:00:27,968 --> 00:00:29,966
Come sit here. It's your favorite spot.

4
00:00:42,976 --> 00:00:43,929
I miss you so much.

5
00:00:44,744 --> 00:00:46,203
Say something true for once.

6
00:00:49,647 --> 00:00:50,832
Why did you go see Wayu at the bar?

7
00:00:52,284 --> 00:00:53,120
Wow.

8
00:00:53,824 --> 00:00:55,252
Are you really that protective
over the new guy?

9
00:00:55,746 --> 00:00:56,667
How do you know Wayu?

10
00:00:57,696 --> 00:00:58,777
What are you trying to do?

11
00:00:58,944 --> 00:01:02,246
Huh, are you grilling me
right now, Krit?

12
00:01:04,112 --> 00:01:05,738
I'm not a suspect, though.

13
00:01:07,584 --> 00:01:08,396
Even so...

14
00:01:28,352 --> 00:01:29,291
Hand over the evidence.

15
00:01:30,277 --> 00:01:31,291
That's cute.

16
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,112
It's obvious you like this one.

17
00:01:40,512 --> 00:01:42,431
Your type is really easy to spot.

18
00:01:45,472 --> 00:01:46,857
I could tell from the moment we met.

19
00:01:48,116 --> 00:01:49,365
Someone with a beautiful smile.

20
00:01:50,208 --> 00:01:51,224
Bright and cheerful.

21
00:01:54,467 --> 00:01:55,364
Simply put.

22
00:01:56,944 --> 00:01:58,286
You like someone like me.

23
00:02:02,330 --> 00:02:04,282
(University, Year 2)

24
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:05,799
Ugh!

25
00:02:08,448 --> 00:02:10,783
Sorry, we opened the door
at the same time.

26
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:16,160
Thank you for agreeing to be my model.

27
00:02:16,704 --> 00:02:18,581
I didn't think Rose would actually
be able to find someone for me.

28
00:02:20,864 --> 00:02:21,669
Yes.

29
00:02:22,792 --> 00:02:25,481
I just wanted to try something new.

30
00:02:26,948 --> 00:02:28,812
Alright, this way please.

31
00:02:34,144 --> 00:02:35,585
Krit, you study law, right?

32
00:02:38,180 --> 00:02:39,177
Yes.

33
00:02:41,851 --> 00:02:44,969
No taking your shirt off,
no bare chest, so don't worry.

34
00:02:45,376 --> 00:02:48,948
The assignment this time is just
to draw a real person, that's all.

35
00:02:49,687 --> 00:02:51,628
So what do I need to do?

36
00:02:52,768 --> 00:02:53,938
Just sit there and look handsome.

37
00:02:55,424 --> 00:03:01,033
Uh, could you unbutton one for me?
It's feeling a little tight.

38
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:04,544
I thought you said no bare chest.

39
00:03:04,768 --> 00:03:08,490
Uh, let me rephrase that.

40
00:03:35,614 --> 00:03:38,570
Krit, have you ever had a partner,
or ever been in love?

41
00:03:42,336 --> 00:03:44,985
For this drawing, I want the eyes
of someone in love.

42
00:03:45,344 --> 00:03:47,878
And I want a sense of care in them too.

43
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:52,881
Then try thinking of someone you like,
or your ideal type.

44
00:04:01,008 --> 00:04:02,014
That's good.

45
00:04:06,912 --> 00:04:10,074
Once I've submitted it to the professor,
I'll give you the picture.

46
00:04:12,431 --> 00:04:13,514
Can I get your Line ID?

47
00:04:13,888 --> 00:04:14,841
Hmm.

48
00:04:16,369 --> 00:04:17,393
Sure.

49
00:04:36,224 --> 00:04:37,120
- You.
- Hmm?

50
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,332
I don't know what to write.

51
00:04:39,072 --> 00:04:40,800
Hey, write this down.

52
00:04:42,208 --> 00:04:43,211
What?

53
00:04:43,456 --> 00:04:45,349
I've got the topic written down for you.

54
00:04:46,901 --> 00:04:47,552
What are you guys doing?

55
00:04:47,872 --> 00:04:48,813
Oh.

56
00:04:51,776 --> 00:04:52,734
We're working on an essay.

57
00:04:53,955 --> 00:04:56,110
The topic is Future Plans
like the professor mentioned.

58
00:04:57,184 --> 00:04:57,888
Have you come up with anything yet?

59
00:04:57,888 --> 00:04:58,944
Hmm.

60
00:04:58,944 --> 00:05:00,142
I wrote that I want to be an actor.

61
00:05:00,142 --> 00:05:01,441
Are you serious?

62
00:05:02,304 --> 00:05:03,661
What part of me doesn't look
serious to you?

63
00:05:03,936 --> 00:05:04,725
I'm serious.

64
00:05:07,456 --> 00:05:08,815
Well, if you want to be one,

65
00:05:09,587 --> 00:05:10,702
you will definitely become one.

66
00:05:15,392 --> 00:05:16,365
Whoops.

67
00:05:19,904 --> 00:05:20,759
Just like I promised.

68
00:05:22,010 --> 00:05:24,716
Whoa, it looks exactly like you.

69
00:05:25,088 --> 00:05:26,907
Honestly, this might even look
better than the real you.

70
00:05:27,648 --> 00:05:28,816
Tsk.

71
00:05:32,224 --> 00:05:33,096
But it's weird.

72
00:05:33,745 --> 00:05:35,151
Seeing my face like that.

73
00:05:39,776 --> 00:05:42,721
Here, look, I even signed it.

74
00:05:44,810 --> 00:05:46,866
Rose, can I ask for some advice?

75
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,760
Mm-hmm.

76
00:05:54,653 --> 00:05:57,359
So, what are you going to write, Krit?

77
00:06:00,072 --> 00:06:00,998
I'm not sure.

78
00:06:02,081 --> 00:06:03,452
Probably something about...

79
00:06:04,034 --> 00:06:05,789
Taking the police exam
as my dad planned.

80
00:06:08,215 --> 00:06:09,399
What about your own dream, Krit?

81
00:06:14,585 --> 00:06:15,777
Don't have any.

82
00:06:19,433 --> 00:06:21,497
Someone once told me

83
00:06:22,082 --> 00:06:23,651
that sometimes our dreams

84
00:06:24,413 --> 00:06:25,814
can be for someone else too.

85
00:06:26,592 --> 00:06:28,503
Supporting someone else's dream.

86
00:06:29,361 --> 00:06:31,462
Krit, do you want to help
make my dream come true?

87
00:06:31,934 --> 00:06:33,290
You could be my manager.

88
00:06:40,889 --> 00:06:41,904
Just a manager?

89
00:06:49,184 --> 00:06:50,821
Actually, you can be more than that.

90
00:06:51,936 --> 00:06:53,108
I'm okay.

91
00:07:06,048 --> 00:07:07,729
Finally.

92
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:12,279
You guys owe me a thank you.

93
00:07:12,279 --> 00:07:15,182
I'm the cupid who brought
you two together.

94
00:07:17,536 --> 00:07:18,464
Way to ruin the moment.

95
00:07:18,464 --> 00:07:19,232
Mm.

96
00:07:19,232 --> 00:07:20,399
You should go. Time for class.

97
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:21,727
Alright, I'll go.

98
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:22,845
Heh.

99
00:07:52,926 --> 00:07:54,259
(University, Year 4)
Where are you taking me?

100
00:07:54,797 --> 00:07:55,986
Just a little father.

101
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:58,750
Ah.

102
00:07:59,744 --> 00:08:00,448
Ready yet?

103
00:08:00,448 --> 00:08:01,173
Mm.

104
00:08:02,024 --> 00:08:03,856
One, two, three.

105
00:08:17,472 --> 00:08:18,409
Wow.

106
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:21,183
You're quite a rebel.

107
00:08:21,204 --> 00:08:23,665
We're not even together yet, and you
already want to move in with me?

108
00:08:25,867 --> 00:08:26,764
Pete.

109
00:08:28,448 --> 00:08:30,143
Even if we have to keep it
from our families,

110
00:08:30,912 --> 00:08:32,310
I still want to tell you this.

111
00:08:34,777 --> 00:08:36,086
I bought this condo.

112
00:08:39,189 --> 00:08:40,677
And I've already transferred it
into your name.

113
00:08:42,716 --> 00:08:44,000
It's a gift for us becoming a couple.

114
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,134
Uh.

115
00:08:47,018 --> 00:08:48,751
Did you really have to go this far?

116
00:08:48,751 --> 00:08:49,992
(Registration Index)

117
00:08:51,318 --> 00:08:52,566
Now that we're together,

118
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:54,949
let's stay like this forever.

119
00:08:56,215 --> 00:08:56,918
Mm.

120
00:09:01,056 --> 00:09:02,372
Uh, Krit...

121
00:09:02,784 --> 00:09:03,446
Hmm?

122
00:09:03,446 --> 00:09:04,759
Actually...

123
00:09:05,544 --> 00:09:07,714
I have something important
to tell you too.

124
00:09:09,387 --> 00:09:11,432
I passed my first casting.

125
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:14,962
- Really?
- Hmm.

126
00:09:15,577 --> 00:09:17,053
- Ha.
- Haha.

127
00:09:18,592 --> 00:09:21,344
When I become famous and win an award,

128
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:23,522
I won't forget to say
your name up there.

129
00:09:23,796 --> 00:09:24,970
You've said it.

130
00:09:24,970 --> 00:09:26,278
Promise.

131
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:27,581
Ah.

132
00:09:28,677 --> 00:09:29,807
Aha.

133
00:09:30,144 --> 00:09:31,027
Mm.

134
00:09:31,401 --> 00:09:32,064
Thank you.

135
00:09:32,064 --> 00:09:33,822
Mm. Thank you too.

136
00:09:35,059 --> 00:09:39,679
(Three Years Later)

137
00:09:39,775 --> 00:09:48,192
(Rising Star Actor of the Year Award,
Khanit Setthaworn, March 7, 2017)

138
00:09:48,192 --> 00:09:50,944
Krit, get out! Get out now!
Talking to you is pointless.

139
00:09:50,944 --> 00:09:53,312
Pete, can you listen to me first?

140
00:09:54,058 --> 00:09:55,616
Listen to what, Krit?

141
00:09:55,616 --> 00:09:57,349
I have already told you
that we're breaking up.

142
00:09:58,003 --> 00:09:59,520
You don't give me any reason.

143
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:01,365
- What did I do wrong? Tell me.
- Why?

144
00:10:01,696 --> 00:10:03,520
We're just not right
for each other, Krit.

145
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:04,761
We're not right together.

146
00:10:05,253 --> 00:10:06,944
I can't endure this any longer.

147
00:10:06,944 --> 00:10:09,216
Pete, seriously, what's happened?

148
00:10:09,216 --> 00:10:11,456
Does the agency know about us, or what?

149
00:10:12,301 --> 00:10:16,018
I don't want to be in this unclear
relationship anymore, Krit.

150
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:19,840
I can't take it anymore. I don't know
how long you will keep your promise.

151
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:21,120
Can you endure a little longer?

152
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,432
- What else should endure?
- Just give me more time.

153
00:10:22,432 --> 00:10:24,256
- Please.
- Krit...

154
00:10:24,256 --> 00:10:26,496
Please give me a little more time, Pete.

155
00:10:27,024 --> 00:10:27,776
Krit.

156
00:10:28,599 --> 00:10:30,023
It's impossible.

157
00:10:30,144 --> 00:10:31,696
One way or another,
you have to marry Rose.

158
00:10:33,317 --> 00:10:35,235
Your dream is never going to come true.

159
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:36,711
Because you

160
00:10:37,149 --> 00:10:38,595
only ever live for your father's dream.

161
00:10:39,008 --> 00:10:40,769
Pete... Pete.

162
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:46,052
Or have you already wanted to break up
with me, using this as an excuse?

163
00:10:46,144 --> 00:10:49,153
Huh? Did the manager scold about
having a boyfriend again?

164
00:10:50,432 --> 00:10:51,904
Or what? Or...

165
00:10:51,904 --> 00:10:55,744
Or is it because I'm not enough
for you? Do you want more than this?

166
00:10:55,744 --> 00:10:58,713
- What do you want? House? Car? Tell me...
- Krit.

167
00:10:59,584 --> 00:11:01,042
Talking like that is insulting.

168
00:11:02,667 --> 00:11:03,938
Get out, Krit.

169
00:11:05,194 --> 00:11:06,752
If you're going to
talk like that, get out.

170
00:11:06,752 --> 00:11:07,264
- No.
- Go.

171
00:11:07,264 --> 00:11:08,192
- No.
- Go.

172
00:11:08,192 --> 00:11:08,869
- No.
- Go.

173
00:11:08,869 --> 00:11:10,144
Pete, please.

174
00:11:10,368 --> 00:11:12,608
Please, can we just
talk this out? Please.

175
00:11:12,608 --> 00:11:13,549
- Please...
- About this room,

176
00:11:14,004 --> 00:11:15,573
you have already transferred it
into my name, right?

177
00:11:17,293 --> 00:11:18,936
Get out of my room right now.

178
00:11:19,796 --> 00:11:20,720
Get out.

179
00:11:22,208 --> 00:11:22,900
Pete.

180
00:11:24,415 --> 00:11:25,434
Pete.

181
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:28,851
Can we come out
and talk this through first?

182
00:11:30,779 --> 00:11:31,955
Pete.

183
00:11:35,184 --> 00:11:36,138
Pete.

184
00:11:38,557 --> 00:11:39,490
Pete.

185
00:12:09,664 --> 00:12:10,314
Krit.

186
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:14,206
You still have the pictures
I drew for you, right?

187
00:12:16,502 --> 00:12:17,422
What do you want?

188
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,784
Just spit it out.

189
00:12:22,702 --> 00:12:23,838
Hmm.

190
00:12:24,992 --> 00:12:25,952
Pixie.

191
00:12:27,616 --> 00:12:28,652
My bar.

192
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:32,378
There's a case now.

193
00:12:32,378 --> 00:12:35,977
A VIP guest was arrested
on drug charges.

194
00:12:36,971 --> 00:12:38,215
Got arrested right at the bar.

195
00:12:41,024 --> 00:12:42,244
You surely won't be cruel.

196
00:12:43,466 --> 00:12:46,047
Are you letting me get caught
for something I didn't do?

197
00:12:56,928 --> 00:12:58,569
Krit, can you really handle this

198
00:12:59,926 --> 00:13:01,738
if you won't help this old lover?

199
00:13:10,592 --> 00:13:12,666
I still want to get back
together with you, Krit.

200
00:13:16,616 --> 00:13:19,056
I never forgot the times
we were together.

201
00:13:20,891 --> 00:13:21,984
You feel the same way, right?

202
00:13:33,831 --> 00:13:38,939
=Love of Silom=

203
00:13:40,192 --> 00:13:41,503
Mm-hmm.

204
00:13:42,336 --> 00:13:43,694
I will always love you

205
00:13:44,512 --> 00:13:46,741
even though we're not together anymore.

206
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:55,255
Mm.

207
00:14:05,184 --> 00:14:07,712
Mm-hmm.

208
00:14:10,299 --> 00:14:11,136
You. Why?

209
00:14:11,136 --> 00:14:12,128
- Why don't you
- Oops.

210
00:14:12,128 --> 00:14:12,864
- turn down the volume?
- Ouch.

211
00:14:12,907 --> 00:14:14,144
- It's bothering me.
- Ouch.

212
00:14:14,144 --> 00:14:15,411
- I don't want to hear it, Tai.
- What's with you?

213
00:14:15,411 --> 00:14:17,330
Shh. Don't be moody.

214
00:14:17,664 --> 00:14:21,344
I'm looking into it, figuring out
what's going on between Pete and Krit.

215
00:14:21,344 --> 00:14:22,944
Then why are you watching his series?

216
00:14:22,944 --> 00:14:25,280
Because it's good.
I can't stop watching it.

217
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:26,835
Hey, but they're acting really well.

218
00:14:27,584 --> 00:14:28,537
Hey, Tai.

219
00:14:28,704 --> 00:14:30,790
If you can't help me,

220
00:14:30,790 --> 00:14:34,525
at least put on earbuds or turn it down
or something. I don't want to watch it.

221
00:14:34,525 --> 00:14:37,344
Hey, don't underestimate my eagle eyes.

222
00:14:37,344 --> 00:14:38,806
Even if I'm just casually watching,

223
00:14:39,328 --> 00:14:41,781
I can totally see why Krit

224
00:14:42,132 --> 00:14:43,429
keeps hanging around you.

225
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:47,058
Why is that?

226
00:14:49,096 --> 00:14:51,099
Because Pete and you

227
00:14:51,099 --> 00:14:52,250
have the same vibe.

228
00:14:52,250 --> 00:14:55,551
I think your police guy is probably
weak to this style.

229
00:14:56,704 --> 00:14:57,676
Your kind of style.

230
00:14:58,112 --> 00:14:59,023
But still...

231
00:14:59,608 --> 00:15:00,859
That doesn't mean he likes you.

232
00:15:01,184 --> 00:15:02,235
I think you should

233
00:15:02,589 --> 00:15:03,739
let it go.

234
00:15:03,739 --> 00:15:06,112
Whoa. Total deja vu.

235
00:15:06,528 --> 00:15:07,952
Feels like I've said this
ten times already.

236
00:15:10,496 --> 00:15:12,621
Ten times? Deja vu?

237
00:15:12,621 --> 00:15:14,126
- You're overplaying it.
- Hey.

238
00:15:14,126 --> 00:15:15,985
- You keep overplaying it, fool.
- Ouch.

239
00:15:16,032 --> 00:15:17,617
I mean it. I'm not kidding around.

240
00:15:18,304 --> 00:15:19,521
Your police guy

241
00:15:19,947 --> 00:15:21,178
has too many secrets.

242
00:15:21,812 --> 00:15:24,352
First there's Rose, and now Pete too?

243
00:15:25,408 --> 00:15:26,706
Just let it go.

244
00:15:37,184 --> 00:15:38,009
Mm.

245
00:15:39,886 --> 00:15:41,150
I've made up my mind, buddy.

246
00:15:41,150 --> 00:15:42,917
Yeah, that's how it should be.

247
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:44,253
My friend.

248
00:15:44,701 --> 00:15:45,847
Love yourself, man.

249
00:15:46,189 --> 00:15:47,136
Yeah.

250
00:15:47,648 --> 00:15:48,488
Good.

251
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:51,728
I've made my decision.

252
00:15:52,037 --> 00:15:53,674
That I'll move forward with Krit.

253
00:15:54,272 --> 00:15:57,062
I can't help it. I'm really weak
when it comes to him.

254
00:15:57,421 --> 00:15:58,422
Hey!

255
00:15:59,416 --> 00:16:00,694
You'll get over it soon.

256
00:16:00,928 --> 00:16:04,058
A handsome guy, good status,
noble family, warm-hearted.

257
00:16:04,058 --> 00:16:05,536
He's not the only one out there. Hey!

258
00:16:05,536 --> 00:16:07,316
Ouch! I'm not listening!

259
00:16:09,786 --> 00:16:11,086
There you go.

260
00:16:12,608 --> 00:16:14,165
Why'd you stop my machine, huh?

261
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:16,963
If I can't make you stop loving him,

262
00:16:17,056 --> 00:16:18,771
I'll just stop your treadmill instead.

263
00:16:20,634 --> 00:16:23,720
The day you cry, I'm not
comforting you at all.

264
00:16:24,036 --> 00:16:26,038
I might even hit you.

265
00:16:26,782 --> 00:16:28,012
Understand?

266
00:16:38,546 --> 00:16:43,072
(Wayu: Who is Pete?)

267
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:45,715
Wayu.

268
00:16:46,784 --> 00:16:47,584
Huh?

269
00:16:48,064 --> 00:16:49,216
Huh, what?

270
00:16:49,216 --> 00:16:50,536
What are you daydreaming about?

271
00:16:50,536 --> 00:16:52,354
No, I'm not really daydreaming.

272
00:16:53,101 --> 00:16:55,006
What are you spacing out about? Tell me.

273
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:57,157
Uh, it's nothing, Mind.

274
00:16:57,157 --> 00:17:01,998
Just spacing out. Maybe TikTok
gave me a short attention span.

275
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:04,107
Yeah, I'm the same.

276
00:17:07,478 --> 00:17:09,110
Oh, where did your friends all go?

277
00:17:09,216 --> 00:17:11,170
They all left.

278
00:17:11,552 --> 00:17:14,904
Come on.

279
00:17:15,328 --> 00:17:16,724
Or is it

280
00:17:16,724 --> 00:17:19,904
that you planned on coming alone
all along, Mind?

281
00:17:19,904 --> 00:17:21,322
Oh, come on.

282
00:17:21,873 --> 00:17:23,200
So you caught me, huh?

283
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,483
Mm-hmm.

284
00:17:24,483 --> 00:17:26,376
You've been coming here pretty often.

285
00:17:26,376 --> 00:17:28,736
Do you get something going on
with my friend or what?

286
00:17:28,736 --> 00:17:30,464
And if I do,

287
00:17:30,981 --> 00:17:31,981
would that be okay?

288
00:17:32,224 --> 00:17:32,998
Tsk.

289
00:17:35,712 --> 00:17:36,866
Sure.

290
00:17:37,541 --> 00:17:40,666
Seriously, if there's anything
you want, just tell me.

291
00:17:40,896 --> 00:17:41,909
Mm.

292
00:17:43,552 --> 00:17:44,672
Gladly.

293
00:17:44,832 --> 00:17:47,856
Whew, you're really something, Mind.

294
00:17:48,017 --> 00:17:49,012
Whew.

295
00:17:49,344 --> 00:17:50,688
Come on! Let's have a toast.

296
00:17:50,743 --> 00:17:52,020
- Ah.
- Come on! Let's go.

297
00:17:52,020 --> 00:17:53,932
- Ah, cheers.
- Let's go.

298
00:17:53,952 --> 00:17:56,445
- Bottoms up.
- Mmm.

299
00:17:56,625 --> 00:17:57,658
Okay.

300
00:17:57,658 --> 00:17:59,646
Please take care of this for me
Take care of my friend too.

301
00:18:00,206 --> 00:18:01,134
Sure.

302
00:18:01,657 --> 00:18:02,324
Yeah.

303
00:18:09,408 --> 00:18:12,516
Hehe... Haha...

304
00:18:12,518 --> 00:18:13,599
- Huh?
- Cheers.

305
00:18:21,531 --> 00:18:22,151
Let's switch places.

306
00:18:23,774 --> 00:18:24,815
Come on. Let's switch places.

307
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:34,087
If you sit over here,

308
00:18:34,678 --> 00:18:35,949
no one will see your face.

309
00:18:36,832 --> 00:18:38,351
You won't have to worry
about being scolded.

310
00:18:43,968 --> 00:18:44,742
Ah.

311
00:18:45,344 --> 00:18:46,774
Come on, then.

312
00:18:49,096 --> 00:18:49,792
What?

313
00:18:49,792 --> 00:18:50,658
Rock, paper, scissors.

314
00:18:51,260 --> 00:18:52,106
No need.

315
00:18:52,608 --> 00:18:54,568
Just relax and have fun today.

316
00:18:54,568 --> 00:18:55,377
Let me entertain you.

317
00:18:59,616 --> 00:19:02,406
Thank you so much, Mind,
for being so nice to me.

318
00:19:03,923 --> 00:19:04,714
But...

319
00:19:05,344 --> 00:19:07,363
I can't let you entertain me.

320
00:19:08,703 --> 00:19:09,764
It'd be bad for the host's image.

321
00:19:10,656 --> 00:19:12,191
I'm okay.

322
00:19:12,774 --> 00:19:13,897
Really, I'm okay.

323
00:19:16,676 --> 00:19:18,114
Today, you should just

324
00:19:19,128 --> 00:19:20,286
drink as much as you want.

325
00:19:20,878 --> 00:19:22,691
And feel whatever you really feel.

326
00:19:24,465 --> 00:19:25,273
Can I ask for this?

327
00:19:26,185 --> 00:19:27,409
Not in a friend's vibe.

328
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:30,291
But real friends.

329
00:19:35,040 --> 00:19:35,754
Sure.

330
00:19:36,448 --> 00:19:37,977
Come on. Cheers.

331
00:19:38,694 --> 00:19:39,616
Here.

332
00:19:39,616 --> 00:19:41,552
- Refill first.
- Oh.

333
00:19:41,552 --> 00:19:44,009
(Supanut Tosakan, 32, Famous
TV producer; Thitiphong, 33)

334
00:19:44,009 --> 00:19:45,568
From what I've dug up,

335
00:19:45,568 --> 00:19:46,780
this guy is Nut's right-hand man.

336
00:19:46,780 --> 00:19:49,280
Hehe. A perfect scapegoat, Captain.

337
00:19:49,472 --> 00:19:51,123
There's even evidence
of money transfers.

338
00:19:51,123 --> 00:19:53,065
(Thai police are dedicated to public safety)
His wife and kids moved overseas.

339
00:19:53,724 --> 00:19:54,879
What do we do next, Captain?

340
00:19:56,428 --> 00:19:57,869
Once we let the bait go,

341
00:19:59,072 --> 00:20:00,663
it'll lead us straight to its nest.

342
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:16,735
Please inform the team.

343
00:20:17,511 --> 00:20:19,221
Once we get there,
we move in immediately.

344
00:20:21,216 --> 00:20:22,092
Understood.

345
00:20:27,464 --> 00:20:28,283
Captain.

346
00:20:28,283 --> 00:20:29,984
If I asked your informant

347
00:20:29,984 --> 00:20:31,475
to keep digging into Nut,

348
00:20:31,475 --> 00:20:32,287
would that be possible?

349
00:20:32,287 --> 00:20:34,240
I noticed he's still showing up
at other parties.

350
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:35,904
We might be able to
get more evidence that way.

351
00:20:35,904 --> 00:20:36,942
Sergeant.

352
00:20:36,942 --> 00:20:38,736
We can't keep relying on other people.

353
00:20:38,736 --> 00:20:40,047
This job is dangerous.

354
00:20:40,075 --> 00:20:41,467
It has to be our responsibility.

355
00:20:41,852 --> 00:20:42,603
Yes, sir.

356
00:20:43,454 --> 00:20:46,212
Wow. You made the deal yourself.
Why are you getting mad?

357
00:20:48,909 --> 00:20:55,688
(Drug Case Suspect)

358
00:20:58,752 --> 00:21:03,128
(Wayu: Who is Pete?)

359
00:21:03,128 --> 00:21:05,248
(Krit: Your evidence has really
moved the case forward)

360
00:21:05,356 --> 00:21:10,050
(Krit: Thanks so much)

361
00:21:29,152 --> 00:21:31,282
Why are you here?

362
00:21:34,176 --> 00:21:35,177
Well...

363
00:21:36,736 --> 00:21:39,040
Today's the day you get the doctor's
diagnosis result, isn't it?

364
00:21:40,384 --> 00:21:41,281
Yeah.

365
00:21:41,961 --> 00:21:42,913
Then why are you here?

366
00:21:44,117 --> 00:21:45,479
The teacher called me.

367
00:21:46,667 --> 00:21:48,768
She probably thought I was his parent.

368
00:21:51,744 --> 00:21:53,264
You're not the actual parent.

369
00:21:54,171 --> 00:21:55,344
Then why did you come?

370
00:21:57,025 --> 00:21:58,696
I may not be your family,

371
00:21:59,343 --> 00:22:01,587
but I'm the one taking care
of all your expenses, Wayu.

372
00:22:02,411 --> 00:22:03,994
So I think I have a right to know.

373
00:22:08,113 --> 00:22:09,805
The doctor is ready, sir.

374
00:22:09,805 --> 00:22:11,235
Is now a good time?

375
00:22:11,235 --> 00:22:12,723
Sure thing. We're all set.

376
00:22:13,163 --> 00:22:14,080
Okay, sir.

377
00:22:14,080 --> 00:22:15,164
Um...

378
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:16,974
I'm the father.

379
00:22:17,984 --> 00:22:18,816
He's not.

380
00:22:19,008 --> 00:22:19,776
I'm the foster father.

381
00:22:20,544 --> 00:22:22,880
Oh, I see. Then I will

382
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,736
make a note of that in the record.

383
00:22:24,736 --> 00:22:25,970
Sure, thank you.

384
00:22:25,970 --> 00:22:26,999
Please go ahead, doctor.

385
00:22:34,623 --> 00:22:37,600
So, the parent can talk
to the doctor comfortably.

386
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:39,744
As for Singto, I'll take care of him.

387
00:22:39,746 --> 00:22:40,866
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

388
00:22:42,308 --> 00:22:43,360
Hello, doctor.

389
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:44,177
Hello.

390
00:22:44,177 --> 00:22:45,153
Hello.

391
00:22:45,621 --> 00:22:47,084
How is Singto doing?

392
00:22:47,550 --> 00:22:50,202
Based on the diagnosis results,
there's nothing to worry about.

393
00:22:50,202 --> 00:22:54,267
His developmental delay isn't caused
by any brain abnormality,

394
00:22:54,267 --> 00:22:55,551
or any physical condition.

395
00:22:55,551 --> 00:22:57,623
He can definitely improve.

396
00:22:57,623 --> 00:23:00,254
But he'll need people
to talk to him often.

397
00:23:00,254 --> 00:23:04,501
Try telling him stories or reading him
storybooks. That'll help a lot.

398
00:23:05,831 --> 00:23:06,821
Okay, doctor.

399
00:23:06,821 --> 00:23:07,826
And...

400
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:10,158
Is there anything we should be
especially careful about?

401
00:23:11,438 --> 00:23:13,697
Hmm. Not really.

402
00:23:13,697 --> 00:23:15,496
He just needs time,

403
00:23:15,516 --> 00:23:17,212
and a little extra care and attention.

404
00:23:18,767 --> 00:23:23,901
But I understand that you both work,
so time might be a bit tight.

405
00:23:23,901 --> 00:23:27,776
Still, if you both work together,
it'll definitely help.

406
00:23:28,512 --> 00:23:30,573
Ah, sorry.

407
00:23:30,784 --> 00:23:32,128
Just one person, not two.

408
00:23:32,202 --> 00:23:33,657
Two is right.

409
00:23:33,657 --> 00:23:34,720
We're helping each other out.

410
00:23:36,359 --> 00:23:37,799
Family

411
00:23:37,799 --> 00:23:40,203
is the very first foundation.

412
00:23:40,203 --> 00:23:41,414
Especially for children

413
00:23:41,414 --> 00:23:44,262
like Singto, who need special care.

414
00:23:44,262 --> 00:23:47,154
So both of you need to
help take care of him.

415
00:23:47,154 --> 00:23:50,742
Don't let your arguments
or stress affect the child.

416
00:23:50,742 --> 00:23:52,223
Okay, sir?

417
00:23:52,223 --> 00:23:53,536
Okay, sir?

418
00:23:53,536 --> 00:23:55,158
Otherwise, things will only get worse.

419
00:23:56,317 --> 00:23:57,182
Yes.

420
00:23:57,820 --> 00:23:59,981
We'll take even better care of Singto.

421
00:23:59,981 --> 00:24:01,357
Anyway,

422
00:24:01,780 --> 00:24:03,668
please take care of Singto, doctor.

423
00:24:03,668 --> 00:24:04,730
I just want him

424
00:24:05,127 --> 00:24:06,528
to start talking soon.

425
00:24:07,631 --> 00:24:08,878
Of course.

426
00:24:08,878 --> 00:24:11,099
Let's set up a follow-up.
Then I'll update you again.

427
00:24:11,099 --> 00:24:12,117
Sure.

428
00:24:12,532 --> 00:24:13,613
Thank you, doctor.

429
00:24:13,613 --> 00:24:14,240
Thank you.

430
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:15,096
Thank you.

431
00:24:41,920 --> 00:24:42,688
Yeah!

432
00:24:42,688 --> 00:24:43,762
Let's do the yellow one first.

433
00:24:44,496 --> 00:24:46,171
Good. Now the green one.

434
00:24:46,171 --> 00:24:46,990
Come here.

435
00:24:47,456 --> 00:24:49,049
Oh, there.

436
00:24:49,568 --> 00:24:50,503
Yeah!

437
00:24:51,136 --> 00:24:52,091
Eww.

438
00:24:52,091 --> 00:24:53,985
Come on. Sit here.

439
00:24:53,985 --> 00:24:56,262
You're busy, aren't you?
Go back to your case.

440
00:24:56,262 --> 00:24:57,899
I'll take Singto home.

441
00:24:58,035 --> 00:25:00,094
I'm not busy anymore, Wayu.

442
00:25:00,852 --> 00:25:02,422
I've finished all my work for today.

443
00:25:05,165 --> 00:25:06,016
Singto.

444
00:25:06,496 --> 00:25:07,467
Singto.

445
00:25:07,467 --> 00:25:09,536
Singto, come on. Say "Papa."

446
00:25:09,536 --> 00:25:11,904
- Papa.
- Papa. Well done!

447
00:25:11,904 --> 00:25:13,248
Which one is "Papa"?
Point it out quickly.

448
00:25:13,248 --> 00:25:14,016
(Papa)

449
00:25:14,016 --> 00:25:15,316
Well done!

450
00:25:16,749 --> 00:25:18,137
Singto remembers it now.

451
00:25:21,111 --> 00:25:22,912
Alright then. Singto.

452
00:25:22,912 --> 00:25:24,727
- Say "Dad." Come on. Say "Dad."
- Dad.

453
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:26,182
(Papa, Dad)
Well done!

454
00:25:26,976 --> 00:25:27,712
Ah.

455
00:25:27,712 --> 00:25:28,896
From now on,

456
00:25:28,896 --> 00:25:31,084
Singto, call me as "Dad," okay?

457
00:25:31,084 --> 00:25:32,288
Is that okay? "Dad".

458
00:25:32,288 --> 00:25:32,800
Dad.

459
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:34,298
Well done!

460
00:25:37,074 --> 00:25:38,380
Come on. Let's head home now.

461
00:25:38,380 --> 00:25:39,328
Okay, go.

462
00:25:39,328 --> 00:25:40,873
(Papa, Dad)

463
00:25:40,873 --> 00:25:43,123
You can just take back
that whole "Papa" thing.

464
00:25:45,295 --> 00:25:46,374
I'll escort you.

465
00:25:47,436 --> 00:25:49,599
I can get back on my own. No need.

466
00:25:51,832 --> 00:25:53,426
Dad.

467
00:25:53,426 --> 00:25:54,688
Dad.

468
00:25:54,688 --> 00:25:56,870
- Dad.
- Well done!

469
00:26:02,250 --> 00:26:03,471
We've arrived.

470
00:26:04,559 --> 00:26:05,358
Come on.

471
00:26:09,344 --> 00:26:10,536
One, two, three.

472
00:26:11,100 --> 00:26:13,600
Alright, Singto,
take off your shoes first.

473
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:16,978
Hold on. Let me get your bag
off first. Alright, okay.

474
00:26:25,888 --> 00:26:26,844
Why are you still here?

475
00:26:31,439 --> 00:26:33,455
The case only moved forward

476
00:26:34,304 --> 00:26:36,246
because of the evidence you gave us.

477
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:45,629
I was just doing my job.

478
00:26:46,272 --> 00:26:47,311
No need to thank me.

479
00:26:52,512 --> 00:26:53,852
So who exactly is Pete?

480
00:26:59,165 --> 00:27:00,181
He's my ex.

481
00:27:01,542 --> 00:27:03,395
But he has no influence
on my life anymore.

482
00:27:05,920 --> 00:27:07,578
Then why didn't you reply to my message?

483
00:27:09,408 --> 00:27:10,928
Just can't reply like this?

484
00:27:11,833 --> 00:27:13,643
Are you sure he really has no influence?

485
00:27:20,416 --> 00:27:21,834
Teaching others to lie.

486
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:25,629
But you're not very good
at lying yourself, Officer.

487
00:27:26,915 --> 00:27:28,043
I'm not lying about anything.

488
00:27:30,620 --> 00:27:32,321
Then why did Pete come to see me?

489
00:27:33,433 --> 00:27:35,390
And you, what exactly
are you trying to say?

490
00:27:37,618 --> 00:27:39,394
What are you two playing at here, huh?

491
00:27:47,664 --> 00:27:49,376
(Mom)

492
00:27:51,124 --> 00:27:52,036
I should get going.

493
00:27:52,357 --> 00:27:53,258
Sorry.

494
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:56,821
Hello, Mom.

495
00:27:57,962 --> 00:27:59,962
I'm on my way. About 20 minutes.

496
00:28:06,351 --> 00:28:07,772
He's so hard to figure out.

497
00:28:27,065 --> 00:28:28,128
(Far from the Heart by Miteennn)

498
00:28:28,224 --> 00:28:31,104
♪I'm not hooked on coffee,
I'm hooked on you♪

499
00:28:31,104 --> 00:28:33,696
♪I'm not into the sea, I'm into you♪

500
00:28:33,696 --> 00:28:39,072
♪But the thing is,
you still have him in your heart♪

501
00:28:39,072 --> 00:28:42,336
♪I've never dared to ask,
knowing I have no right♪

502
00:28:42,336 --> 00:28:44,864
♪If I get jealous, I know it isn't fair♪

503
00:28:44,864 --> 00:28:47,488
♪Still, I just want to be
a little closer to you♪

504
00:28:47,488 --> 00:28:49,488
♪What should I do?♪

505
00:28:52,321 --> 00:28:53,367
Hey, Krit!

506
00:28:53,999 --> 00:28:55,970
I thought you wouldn't make it back
in time for dinner.

507
00:28:56,457 --> 00:28:57,874
Do I always have to call you?

508
00:28:58,144 --> 00:28:58,916
Mm.

509
00:28:59,711 --> 00:29:00,637
I...

510
00:29:01,184 --> 00:29:02,665
- I went to see Rose.
- Mm.

511
00:29:02,854 --> 00:29:03,968
That's why I'm a bit late.

512
00:29:04,906 --> 00:29:07,687
Actually, Dad and Mom
could've started without me.

513
00:29:07,744 --> 00:29:10,894
How can it be a family dinner
without you, Krit?

514
00:29:12,580 --> 00:29:15,276
So, did you go on a date with Rose?

515
00:29:16,576 --> 00:29:17,724
When's the big news?

516
00:29:19,392 --> 00:29:20,594
Well, probably...

517
00:29:21,504 --> 00:29:22,476
Not yet.

518
00:29:23,392 --> 00:29:24,888
Then when are you
going to take care of it?

519
00:29:25,355 --> 00:29:28,109
You've kept putting it off
until you've reached this age.

520
00:29:28,810 --> 00:29:30,623
How long are you
going to keep her waiting?

521
00:29:31,004 --> 00:29:33,935
A decent man shouldn't drag his feet.

522
00:29:36,418 --> 00:29:37,881
Rose needs time.

523
00:29:38,225 --> 00:29:39,153
Not me.

524
00:29:40,896 --> 00:29:41,808
Hey.

525
00:29:48,416 --> 00:29:50,785
Or are you the reason
she still can't be sure?

526
00:29:53,258 --> 00:29:54,874
Uh, well, Krit...

527
00:29:55,216 --> 00:29:56,357
Dad and Mom,

528
00:29:56,376 --> 00:29:58,184
just want to hold our grandchild.

529
00:29:58,184 --> 00:30:00,972
We're worried we'll be too old
to help raise them.

530
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:07,396
Okay. I'll set the table.
Let's have dinner together.

531
00:30:08,096 --> 00:30:09,070
Okay.

532
00:30:15,107 --> 00:30:16,521
How's the case going?

533
00:30:19,503 --> 00:30:20,749
It's progressed to the next step.

534
00:30:21,056 --> 00:30:22,559
We're going on patrol tonight.

535
00:30:22,559 --> 00:30:24,787
We should get more key evidence.

536
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:28,725
As a commander,

537
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:31,071
you can't be wishy-washy.

538
00:30:32,222 --> 00:30:33,977
If you can't earn their trust,

539
00:30:33,977 --> 00:30:36,394
don't expect to lead anyone.

540
00:30:37,033 --> 00:30:38,914
Just looking at the way you live,

541
00:30:38,914 --> 00:30:41,700
I can already tell what kind
of officer you'll be.

542
00:30:43,531 --> 00:30:47,480
Don't forget you carry this family's
name with you everywhere.

543
00:30:49,985 --> 00:30:53,396
